15 Nov 2016 00:20






It's a lot simpler than that.

+3

-this


You see, in Australia, the invasive carp hit up a body of water, eat everything, multiply drastically, and then they die off because they all starve. It's pretty nasty for the environment and for the carp. While this is set in Canada, and the invasive carp are of a different species, the same principle still applies in that they a) aren't native and b) will eat literally everything. To put it simply, the SCP is supposed to be a source of food that they can always rely on.

The carp were always smart, but they're definitely not infallible. They overdid it a little, and they're doing their best to fix the results of that.








